IN the INTEREST OF: K.M.J., C.D.J. and T.K.E., Plaintiffs. F.S. and D.S., Respondents, Juvenile Officer, Respondent, K.L., Defendant,
v.
J.J., Appellant, K.L., Appellant. WD 80987 CONS. WD 81066 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: March 20, 2018 Kelley Gilmore, Esq., Matthew Branson, Esq. and Stephanie McCabe, for Appellants Robert Arnold, III, for Plaintiffs Mitchell Widener, Esq. and Laurie Snell, Esq., for Respondents Before Division One: Thomas H. Newton, Presiding Judge, Victor C. Howard, Judge and Karen King Mitchell, Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

J.J. appeals the judgment of Jackson County Circuit Court terminating his parental rights. K.L. appeals the judgment denying her petition for adoption of the minor children and granting F.S. and D.S.'s petition for adoption. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
